    The root cause of the stack buffer overflow is an off-by-one error in the   
    for loop condition within the crc8 function.                                
                                                                                
    Analysis of the Defect                                                      
                                                                                
    In program.c, the crc8 function is defined as:                              
                                                                                
                                                                                
     static uint8_t crc8(const uint8_t *buf, size_t len) {                      
         uint8_t crc = 0x00;                                                    
         // ...                                                                 
         for (size_t i = 0; i <= len; i++) { // The error is here               
             crc ^= buf[i];                                                     
             // ...                                                             
         }                                                                      
         return crc;                                                            
     }                                                                          
                                                                                
                                                                                
    The function receives len, which is the correct number of bytes in the      
    input buffer buf. In C, array indexing is zero-based: if a buffer has size  
    len, its valid elements range from buf[0] to buf[len - 1].                  
                                                                                
    The loop condition i <= len causes the loop to iterate from i = 0 to i =    
    len (inclusive). This means when i == len, the code executes crc ^=         
    buf[len]. Since buf only contains valid indices 0 through len-1, accessing  
    buf[len] results in an out-of-bounds read. Because this buf is allocated    
    on the stack in main, the memory access at buf[len] reads the byte          
    immediately following the array on the stack, triggering the stack buffer   
    overflow/sanitizer error.                                                   
                                                                                
    Root-Cause Fix                                                              
                                                                                
    The loop condition should be changed from i <= len (which allows iterating  
    up to len) to i < len (which correctly iterates up to len - 1).             
                                                                                
    Recommendation                                                              
                                                                                
    Change the loop condition in program.c at line 11.                          
                                                                                
    File: program.c Change:                                                     
                                                                                
                                                                                
     -    for (size_t i = 0; i <= len; i++) {                                   
     +    for (size_t i = 0; i < len; i++) {                                    
                                                                                
                                                                                
